U.S. Education Secretary  Arne Duncan 
and ESPN President  John Skipper  will be among the speakers when
National Basketball Association executives meet in Houston today
to examine the relationship between sports and the media.  Dick Costolo , the chief executive officer of Twitter Inc.,
the service that features 140-character status updates, will
discuss the future of media, social networks and content
distribution at the NBAâ€™s 14th annual technology conference.  The program also includes a presentation by F. Michael
Naderi, director of solar system exploration at the National
Aeronautics and Space Administration, on capturing, analyzing
and transmitting high-resolution images from Mars, the NBA said
in a news release.  Other speakers include  Nathan Hubbard , the CEO of
Ticketmaster; and  Claude Ruibal , global head of sports content
for Google Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
